**Abstract:**
Working notes titled "Authorial Voice in Philosophy." Contrasts first-person perspective (Kant, Descartes) with third-person perspective (Skinner) in philosophical writing. Distinguishes the "exposed subject's perspective" from the "pure contemplator's perspective." Proposes two fundamental modes: curiosity (purpose: to know) and concern (purpose: to change the world). Explores relationship between reflective/decisional modes and philosophical method.

**AI Recommendation:** Keep in 1993/ - philosophical working notes

